wi.indAprvSt

We'll use this indAprvSt (likely meaning Indent Approval Status) to determine whether the status is:

Approved тЬЕ

Rejected тЭМ

Pending тМЫ



---

тЬЕ 1. Update your test_2() Function:

Inside the table cell where you show the status, replace this line:

<b>Status</b><br>тЬЕ<br>Approved<br>

with this:

<b>Status</b><br>' . $this->getStatusIcon($indent['indAprvSt']) . '<br>' . $this->getStatusLabel($indent['indAprvSt']) . '<br>


---

ЁЯЫая╕П 2. Add Helper Functions to Your Controller

Just add these two functions inside your controller:

private function getStatusIcon($statusCode) {
    switch ((int)$statusCode) {
        case 50: // Approved
            return 'тЬЕ';
        case 0:  // Pending
            return 'тМЫ';
        case 40: // Rejected (example, adjust based on your logic)
            return 'тЭМ';
        default:
            return 'тЭУ';
    }
}

private function getStatusLabel($statusCode) {
    switch ((int)$statusCode) {
        case 50:
            return 'Approved';
        case 0:
            return 'Pending';
        case 40:
            return 'Rejected';
        default:
            return 'Unknown';
    }
}

> ЁЯТб Note: Adjust the status codes (50, 0, 40) based on how your system encodes them.




---

ЁЯзк Examples:

If indAprvSt is:

50 тЖТ тЬЕ Approved

0 тЖТ тМЫ Pending

40 тЖТ тЭМ Rejected

NULL or unknown тЖТ тЭУ Unknown



